derivation.yuyuan_name: Middle English: from Anglo-Norman French warantie, variant of garantie (see guaranty). Early use was as a legal term denoting a covenant annexed to a conveyance of property, in which the vendor affirmed the security of the title

entry.def: A warranty is a written promise by a company that, if you find a fault in something they have sold you within a certain time, they will repair it or replace it free of charge.

means.word_mean: 1. a written assurance that some product or service will be provided or will meet certain specifications
